quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,What are they asking each other about
  78,2,The awesome news (of the afterlife)
  78,3,"About which they have (many doubts, discords and) disagreements"
  78,4,By no means! They shall soon find out
  78,5,Indeed! They shall soon find out
  78,6,Have We not laid out the earth as a cradle
  78,7,And (nailed) the Mountains (down) as pegs
  78,8,We created you all in pairs
  78,9,We created sleep for you to rest (and rejuvenate)
  78,10,We made the night (dark as) a cloak (that conceals and covers)
  78,11,And We made the day (bright) for (you to earn your) livelihood
  78,12,And We arranged seven (solid and) strong (cosmic systems) over you
  78,13,And We set up (the sun as) a bright and blazing lamp
  78,14,And We sent down plenty of water from the rain clouds
  78,15,"To produce with it, the grains and the plants"
  78,16,And lush and luxurious gardens
  78,17,Certainly! The Day of Decision is a (destined and) definite day
  78,18,You will all emerge in droves on the day the trumpet sounds
  78,19,"And the heavens would be (uncovered and) opened, as if it had (many wide-open) gates"
  78,20,"And the mountains would be (dislodged and) set in motion; they would look like a mirage, (an illusion)"
  78,21,"Hell, in fact, lies in ambush"
  78,22,"For the transgressors, it will become the (abiding) abode"
  78,23,"In it, they will stay for a long stretch of time"
  78,24,"There they will not ever taste, much less drink, anything cool"
  78,25,"(They will drink) only boiling-hot water, and pus (from wounds)"
  78,26,An apt and apposite outcome
  78,27,"Indeed, never did they anticipate a reckoning"
  78,28,And falsely did they oppose Our verses (and signs)
  78,29,We have recorded every single thing in a book
  78,30,Now taste (the consequences of your deeds)! Suffering is all We shall ever bestow _ and increase _ upon you